WEBVTT

00:16.494 --> 00:19.323
[Water lapping]

00:39.604 --> 00:42.259
[Breathing shakily]

01:13.899 --> 01:23.083
♪♪

01:23.083 --> 01:32.266
♪♪

01:32.266 --> 01:41.710
♪♪

01:58.118 --> 02:07.039
♪♪

02:15.918 --> 02:17.224
[Woodpecker pecking]

02:17.224 --> 02:21.706
[Breathing heavily]

02:35.938 --> 02:38.854
Percy: Oh.

02:38.854 --> 02:40.551
[Laughs]

02:41.596 --> 02:43.989
Here I am,
writing you a beautiful sonnet,

02:43.989 --> 02:46.818
in peace, finally leagues
away from our families,

02:46.818 --> 02:48.472
and I get attacked.

02:48.472 --> 02:49.734
Show me.

02:55.653 --> 02:58.787
"An Ode to
Intellectual Beauty."

03:02.051 --> 03:03.879
My love,
it's beautiful.

03:09.319 --> 03:11.147
Shouldn't we have gotten
a carriage to Byron's?

03:11.147 --> 03:13.323
Mary: It's only a 15-minute
walk from our cottage.

03:13.323 --> 03:15.195
Besides, I'm fine.
Don't worry.

03:16.805 --> 03:18.633
Let's enjoy our beautiful
new start.

03:18.633 --> 03:19.938
If you're happy.

03:19.938 --> 03:22.506
Claire:
Sister! Sister!

03:22.506 --> 03:25.640
Mary! Mary!Claire.

03:25.640 --> 03:28.556
Do you think Byron will help me?
Wouldn't that be marvelous?

03:28.556 --> 03:29.861
Help you?

03:29.861 --> 03:31.907
My acting, of course.

03:31.907 --> 03:33.561
I can see it already.

03:33.561 --> 03:35.345
The Western stage.

03:35.345 --> 03:37.086
Ophelia.

03:37.086 --> 03:40.220
No, Desdemona.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.570
And Juliet.

03:42.570 --> 03:46.922
A lovesick teenager destined
for a tragic and violent death.

03:46.922 --> 03:48.924
Now that you mention it,
moppet...

03:48.924 --> 03:50.317
You'll see, Percy.

03:50.317 --> 03:51.622
You'll see.

03:51.622 --> 03:53.189
Do be careful
with him, sister.

03:53.189 --> 03:54.973
Don't forget...

03:54.973 --> 03:59.021
♪♪

03:59.021 --> 04:01.893
She's a haughty
young thing.

04:01.893 --> 04:03.504
Claire, don't run,
sister.

04:03.504 --> 04:04.809
She's excited.

04:04.809 --> 04:06.811
Byron does throw
the best parties.

04:06.811 --> 04:08.770
Oh, we still need
to unpack.

04:08.770 --> 04:10.902
Please enjoy
yourself tonight.

04:10.902 --> 04:13.644
I want you
to like my friends.

04:13.644 --> 04:15.472
You found me!

04:15.472 --> 04:17.344
-Byron.
-Percy!

04:17.344 --> 04:19.868
[Percy Laughs]

04:19.868 --> 04:22.653
Byron: Mwah!

04:22.653 --> 04:24.829
Miss Godwin.

04:24.829 --> 04:26.527
[Smooches]
[Chuckles]

04:26.527 --> 04:28.833
What do you think of
my not-so-humble abode?

04:28.833 --> 04:32.010
Ooh!
Isn't she glorious?

04:32.010 --> 04:33.273
Oh, hello.

04:35.884 --> 04:38.016
Oh, yes.
Yes, you'll do.

04:38.016 --> 04:39.322
Percy: Byron.

04:39.322 --> 04:41.281
In. In.
Tonight, it rains.

04:41.281 --> 04:42.543
Cocktails are inside.

04:42.543 --> 04:45.372
Quickly, before John
drinks them all.

04:45.372 --> 04:46.634
[Laughs]

04:46.634 --> 04:50.638
♪♪

04:50.638 --> 04:53.554
Percy: "One white skull
and seven dry bones,

04:53.554 --> 04:55.773
on the margin of the stones,
where --"

04:55.773 --> 04:59.168
Claire: "Where a few
gray rushes stand,

04:59.168 --> 05:02.519
boundaries of the water
and land."

05:02.519 --> 05:03.955
John: Ah.

05:03.955 --> 05:07.176
Bravo. Bravo.

05:07.176 --> 05:10.875
Bored!
I'm bored!

05:10.875 --> 05:13.225
Why must it rain
incessantly?

05:13.225 --> 05:15.576
It's just
a first draft.

05:15.576 --> 05:17.578
We need excitement.

05:17.578 --> 05:19.275
Terror!

05:19.275 --> 05:21.059
Quick, someone tell me
a ghost story.

05:21.059 --> 05:23.105
No more ghost stories.

05:23.105 --> 05:24.672
Feel my fingers.

05:24.672 --> 05:26.500
I'm already chilled
to the bone.

05:26.500 --> 05:28.676
[Giggles]

05:30.504 --> 05:33.245
I've often thought
how strange it would be

05:33.245 --> 05:36.118
to write something
as dark as a ghost story.

05:36.118 --> 05:38.903
Percy: You'd need to enter
the deepest and...

05:38.903 --> 05:41.950
darkest corners
of your imagination.

05:41.950 --> 05:43.995
I've got it.

05:43.995 --> 05:46.650
A competition.

05:46.650 --> 05:49.131
You may bore me now, my friends,
especially Polidori.

05:49.131 --> 05:51.351
-Doctor --
-But in my benevolence,

05:51.351 --> 05:54.658
I give you the opportunity
to sound your voices.

05:54.658 --> 05:59.620
Lend me your words,
and I'll lend you mine.

05:59.620 --> 06:01.491
But don't be angry
when I leave you...

06:01.491 --> 06:03.014
quivering with fear.

06:03.014 --> 06:06.278
You'd need to awaken
your own nightmares.

06:06.278 --> 06:08.498
-Mm.
-Byron, you're drunk.

06:08.498 --> 06:11.806
Byron: Oh, shut up.
Look, friends!

06:11.806 --> 06:15.026
Right after night.

06:15.026 --> 06:16.724
What do you see
in the darkness?

06:18.682 --> 06:21.772
Percy:
The waves are dead.

06:21.772 --> 06:25.385
The tides are
in their grave.

06:25.385 --> 06:32.217
Darkness doesn't need our help,
only our scrivener.

06:32.217 --> 06:33.610
Come, now, Mary.

06:33.610 --> 06:35.395
Let's get you home.

06:35.395 --> 06:38.093
[Birds chirping]

07:01.333 --> 07:03.248
[Exhales deeply]

07:03.248 --> 07:04.685
[Gasps]

07:08.036 --> 07:09.516
[Breathing heavily]

07:11.909 --> 07:14.738
[Inhales sharply]

07:14.738 --> 07:17.915
[Breathing shakily]

07:17.915 --> 07:19.439
[Groans]

07:21.789 --> 07:24.008
[Breathing shakily]

07:37.239 --> 07:40.024
[Gasps]

07:40.024 --> 07:43.419
No. No. No.

07:43.419 --> 07:44.725
[Inhales sharply]

07:46.248 --> 07:48.729
[Breathing shakily]

07:48.729 --> 07:50.165
Percy.

07:50.165 --> 07:51.949
Percy!

07:51.949 --> 07:53.211
[Body thuds]

07:59.870 --> 08:06.181
[Distant shouting]

08:16.060 --> 08:17.540
Oh!

08:17.540 --> 08:19.020
[Inhales sharply]

08:28.159 --> 08:31.119
[Breathing heavily]

08:34.601 --> 08:37.517
[Breathing heavily]

09:01.366 --> 09:04.326
[Wind whistling]

09:04.326 --> 09:05.849
I've got you, my love.

09:08.417 --> 09:12.116
[Exhales deeply]

09:12.116 --> 09:13.378
I've got you.

09:16.425 --> 09:20.385
She left me.

09:20.385 --> 09:22.431
She's gone.

09:22.431 --> 09:23.998
I know.

09:26.391 --> 09:29.699
[Laughing]

09:29.699 --> 09:31.571
John: Percy --

09:31.571 --> 09:34.574
Byron: Percy, in your expert
opinion, is that a goose, or --

09:34.574 --> 09:37.838
Percy: Hey! Hey!
I can't swim! I can't swim!

09:37.838 --> 09:39.753
-Sink or swim, sport.
-Idiots.

09:39.753 --> 09:41.232
Percy:
It's not funny.

09:41.232 --> 09:52.156
♪♪

09:52.156 --> 09:53.723
Percy: Hey.

09:53.723 --> 09:55.769
Mary.

09:55.769 --> 09:58.249
Hey.

09:58.249 --> 09:59.642
[Inhales shakily]

10:06.823 --> 10:08.085
[Sniffles]

10:08.085 --> 10:09.521
It's alright.

10:09.521 --> 10:11.132
[Inhales shakily]

10:11.132 --> 10:12.612
Look at this.

10:12.612 --> 10:16.311
It's beautiful.

10:16.311 --> 10:19.009
You're beautiful.

10:19.009 --> 10:21.185
Claire: Mary.

10:21.185 --> 10:22.578
Come sit with me.

10:26.016 --> 10:35.678
♪♪

10:35.678 --> 10:37.724
Byron:
Oh. Water me.

10:37.724 --> 10:39.029
I'm parched.

10:39.029 --> 10:40.509
[Claire giggles]

10:41.989 --> 10:43.338
Thank you.

10:47.342 --> 10:50.301
You know, my darling,

10:50.301 --> 10:54.131
I think it's time we get
to know each other better.

10:54.131 --> 11:04.228
♪♪

11:04.228 --> 11:05.621
Percy: Mary.

11:05.621 --> 11:08.276
Mary.

11:08.276 --> 11:11.845
She's a sharp girl,
this new one, eh, Percy?

11:11.845 --> 11:17.024
Though, I must admit,
she's prettier than your wife.

11:17.024 --> 11:19.983
What?
Some sort of wild secret?

11:19.983 --> 11:25.032
Mary, in case you've missed it,
you're the other woman.

11:25.032 --> 11:26.903
The mistress.

11:26.903 --> 11:29.253
You're not quite
Mrs. Shelley.

11:29.253 --> 11:31.255
I am aware.

11:31.255 --> 11:32.561
Thank you.

11:36.696 --> 11:39.133
[Growls]

11:39.133 --> 11:42.092
[Clears throat]
So...

11:42.092 --> 11:44.529
Mary:
I'll be at Byron's.

11:44.529 --> 11:46.401
Percy: Byron, I asked you
to be nice.

11:47.924 --> 11:49.534
[Door opens]

12:09.554 --> 12:12.688
[Indistinct talking]

12:18.607 --> 12:21.218
[Indistinct talking]

12:52.293 --> 13:00.562
♪♪

13:00.562 --> 13:08.831
♪♪

13:08.831 --> 13:10.093
[Man laughs]

13:10.093 --> 13:16.230
♪♪

13:20.147 --> 13:21.757
Mary.

13:21.757 --> 13:28.372
♪♪

13:28.372 --> 13:30.461
Mary.

13:30.461 --> 13:37.425
♪♪

13:37.425 --> 13:44.345
♪♪

13:44.345 --> 13:46.651
"Come...

13:46.651 --> 13:49.306
to me...

13:49.306 --> 13:51.352
in dreams...

13:51.352 --> 13:52.657
my love."

13:55.617 --> 14:00.317
[Mumbles indistinctly]

14:00.317 --> 14:07.324
♪♪

14:07.324 --> 14:14.288
♪♪

14:14.288 --> 14:16.203
[Indistinct talking]

14:16.203 --> 14:19.380
♪♪

14:19.380 --> 14:20.903
[Laughs]

14:20.903 --> 14:28.824
♪♪

14:28.824 --> 14:33.002
"...with...thy kiss."

14:33.002 --> 14:37.398
♪♪

14:37.398 --> 14:38.834
[Gasps][Music stops]

14:45.972 --> 14:48.583
[Distant crying]

15:03.815 --> 15:06.862
[Baby crying]

15:41.244 --> 15:46.032
Percy: Was it the dream
about the door again?

15:46.032 --> 15:47.903
Just before.

15:47.903 --> 15:49.861
But this time,
it finally opened.

15:54.823 --> 15:57.739
Come back to bed, love.
Tell me all about it.

15:57.739 --> 16:00.524
This...

16:00.524 --> 16:04.702
feeling...

16:04.702 --> 16:06.139
I feel like
it's a story.

16:06.139 --> 16:07.401
My story.

16:08.706 --> 16:10.230
[Exhales sharply]

16:10.230 --> 16:14.451
I feel like...

16:14.451 --> 16:16.062
like Michelangelo.

16:16.062 --> 16:17.759
Like Michelangelo?

16:17.759 --> 16:20.022
Chipping away
at a block of marble,

16:20.022 --> 16:22.590
revealing the life inside.

16:22.590 --> 16:23.808
It's already there.

16:23.808 --> 16:25.114
Mm.

16:25.114 --> 16:28.465
I must simply
unleash it.

16:28.465 --> 16:32.513
[Laughs]

16:32.513 --> 16:35.037
God, I sound mad,
don't I?

16:35.037 --> 16:36.778
No. No.

16:40.825 --> 16:44.307
Mary: What?

16:44.307 --> 16:45.613
Come here.

16:45.613 --> 16:51.097
♪♪

16:51.097 --> 16:55.144
What?

16:55.144 --> 16:59.931
There are times, my love,
when I feel that

16:59.931 --> 17:02.195
I'll never feel as powerfully
as you do.

17:02.195 --> 17:10.638
♪♪

17:10.638 --> 17:11.900
[Mary exhales sharply]

17:11.900 --> 17:15.947
♪♪

17:15.947 --> 17:18.124
Mary:
Be gentle with me.

17:18.124 --> 17:19.429
Percy: Always.

17:19.429 --> 17:31.615
♪♪

17:31.615 --> 17:43.758
♪♪

17:43.758 --> 17:50.112
[Piano music playing]

17:50.112 --> 17:51.374
[John clears his throat]

17:51.374 --> 17:54.508
Everyone,
John needs attention.

17:54.508 --> 17:59.165
I have decided
to call it "Vampyre",

17:59.165 --> 18:02.994
a novel by the great
Dr. John Polidori.

18:02.994 --> 18:05.040
I quiver at the thought.

18:05.040 --> 18:07.434
I have no doubt you will,
George.

18:07.434 --> 18:14.876
Because after all,
he's not a man -- not a man.

18:14.876 --> 18:19.881
Instead, a creature who consumes
the blood of humans.

18:19.881 --> 18:21.491
An autobiography, then?

18:21.491 --> 18:24.712
It does sound
remarkably awful, doctor.

18:24.712 --> 18:27.584
Well, tell us how yours
is so much better, then.

18:27.584 --> 18:30.674
Do you even
have one yet?

18:30.674 --> 18:32.459
Well, of course I do.

18:32.459 --> 18:34.200
Go on, Percy.

18:34.200 --> 18:35.549
Scare us.

18:35.549 --> 18:37.028
I wish to tremble.

18:37.028 --> 18:39.727
[Chuckles]

18:39.727 --> 18:41.294
Well...

18:41.294 --> 18:43.948
there were...

18:43.948 --> 18:45.385
three lobsters.

18:47.691 --> 18:50.346
[Laughter]

18:50.346 --> 18:51.652
Ridiculous.

18:51.652 --> 18:53.697
I have nothing.
Um...

18:53.697 --> 18:56.526
But -- But prepare yourselves,
gentlemen,

18:56.526 --> 19:00.965
because it will not be I who
terrorizes your dreams tonight.

19:04.099 --> 19:07.494
Byron:
Well, Mary...

19:07.494 --> 19:08.930
what have you got?

19:08.930 --> 19:10.758
Were you competing,
too, then?

19:10.758 --> 19:15.241
Tell them about your dream,
about Michelangelo.

19:15.241 --> 19:17.373
It's too early
to speak of.

19:17.373 --> 19:18.940
Oh, come now.

19:27.296 --> 19:32.562
There's a hallway,
and a door.

19:32.562 --> 19:35.696
Inside,
the feeling of something...

19:35.696 --> 19:38.133
dead...

19:38.133 --> 19:39.787
yet also alive.

19:41.658 --> 19:46.707
It's the tale of a monster,
a creature who craves love,

19:46.707 --> 19:50.189
but only knows pain
and terror.

19:53.192 --> 19:57.848
Doesn't sound
very scary yet.

19:57.848 --> 19:59.241
It is.

20:03.419 --> 20:04.942
Anyway, it will be...

20:07.945 --> 20:09.643
...assuming I
write it properly.

20:11.732 --> 20:13.429
Now, tell us, Byron,

20:13.429 --> 20:16.780
what have you managed to create
between cocktails?

20:16.780 --> 20:19.218
Byron: Well, it seems
you've already won.

20:21.698 --> 20:23.700
[Footsteps approaching]

21:02.217 --> 21:03.523
Mary: Percy?

21:07.657 --> 21:13.881
"Our sweetest songs are those
that tell of saddest thought."

21:13.881 --> 21:15.796
Oh, my love,
it's heartbreaking.

21:20.714 --> 21:22.585
I didn't mean to, um...

21:26.633 --> 21:30.463
Percy, what's wrong?

21:30.463 --> 21:31.812
Is this from your father?

21:31.812 --> 21:33.117
Percy:
Mary, stop.

21:33.117 --> 21:35.685
[Giggles]
Make me.

21:35.685 --> 21:37.034
Stop.

21:43.606 --> 21:44.868
Percy.

21:46.522 --> 21:48.263
Percy, what does it say?

21:49.699 --> 21:51.092
It's my wife.

21:54.530 --> 21:55.879
Your wife?

21:55.879 --> 21:57.490
Mm.

21:57.490 --> 21:58.882
What has happened?

22:04.366 --> 22:05.976
[Sniffling]

22:11.808 --> 22:13.332
She's dead.

22:17.336 --> 22:19.250
While she was pregnant.

22:22.210 --> 22:25.648
She walked into
the water.

22:25.648 --> 22:27.215
She drowned them both.

22:33.264 --> 22:35.919
I wished her gone
for so long...

22:40.446 --> 22:42.056
...but not like this.

22:49.933 --> 22:52.066
Pregnant?

22:52.066 --> 22:53.589
With your child?

22:55.635 --> 22:58.507
Mary: When you went home
for Christmas?

22:58.507 --> 23:07.298
♪♪

23:07.298 --> 23:15.698
♪♪

23:24.577 --> 23:29.103
♪♪

23:29.103 --> 23:30.539
Woman: Percy.

23:30.539 --> 23:32.236
Percy!

23:32.236 --> 23:39.896
♪♪

23:39.896 --> 23:41.420
Percy:
It's my wife.

23:41.420 --> 23:46.163
♪♪

23:46.163 --> 23:47.730
[Baby crying]

23:47.730 --> 23:50.298
She drowned them both.

23:50.298 --> 23:52.431
[Water running]

23:52.431 --> 24:00.003
♪♪

24:00.003 --> 24:08.185
♪♪

24:38.215 --> 24:39.695
[Laughter]

24:41.654 --> 24:43.046
[Inhales sharply]

24:54.144 --> 24:57.104
[Indistinct talking]

24:57.104 --> 24:58.975
[Exhales deeply]

24:58.975 --> 25:08.942
♪♪

25:08.942 --> 25:10.204
[Inhales shakily]

25:10.204 --> 25:11.510
The body.

25:11.510 --> 25:14.295
♪♪

25:14.295 --> 25:16.384
Then, the doctor...

25:16.384 --> 25:19.822
would be...

25:19.822 --> 25:21.215
here.

25:28.701 --> 25:32.879
"It was this dreary night
in November

25:32.879 --> 25:36.230
where I beheld the
accomplishment of all my work."

25:45.805 --> 25:48.024
[Leaves crunching]

25:58.948 --> 26:01.081
Mary: No one would sell to me
at market.

26:03.823 --> 26:05.955
Mary: Your father has
stopped his payments.

26:14.442 --> 26:16.836
Percy: Yes.

26:16.836 --> 26:18.925
How are we to eat?

26:18.925 --> 26:22.058
I'm a poet.
I'm write for our supper.

26:22.058 --> 26:24.321
But why has your father
stopped payment at all?

26:24.321 --> 26:27.194
He no longer supports
our lifestyle...

26:27.194 --> 26:30.110
unless we get married.

26:30.110 --> 26:32.503
That's it?
Surely, the solut--

26:32.503 --> 26:34.549
No.

26:34.549 --> 26:37.030
I won't marry again.

26:37.030 --> 26:38.292
I won't.

26:44.385 --> 26:47.780
So, I'm to be your
mistress forever?

26:47.780 --> 26:51.174
Abandoned whenever
your mind changes?

26:51.174 --> 26:52.611
[Slams table]

26:52.611 --> 26:57.180
You are my partner for life,
not my mistress.

26:57.180 --> 26:59.879
If you do not trust that,
then seek a better match.

27:01.924 --> 27:04.666
And don't blame me for something
I've never promised you.

27:07.364 --> 27:09.410
[Birds chirping]

27:18.767 --> 27:21.074
[Thunder crashes]

27:26.470 --> 27:28.995
[Wind blowing]

27:41.355 --> 27:43.270
[Door opens]

27:49.580 --> 27:52.366
[Footsteps approaching]

28:03.464 --> 28:04.770
[Smooches]

28:04.770 --> 28:06.467
[Percy moans]

28:09.644 --> 28:12.647
[Grunts]

28:12.647 --> 28:13.996
Percy.

28:19.175 --> 28:20.960
[Percy moans]

28:20.960 --> 28:22.526
Percy.

28:22.526 --> 28:23.789
You're drunk.

28:24.572 --> 28:26.269
[Percy chuckles]

28:26.269 --> 28:28.184
[Sighs]

28:42.068 --> 28:43.417
Percy, stop it.

28:43.417 --> 28:44.679
Percy:
I love you.

28:50.250 --> 28:51.468
[Belt unbuckles]

28:51.468 --> 28:52.731
Percy, stop it.

29:00.608 --> 29:03.654
[Moans]

29:56.838 --> 29:59.014
[Sobbing]

30:03.889 --> 30:05.368
[Inhales shakily]

30:12.114 --> 30:14.725
[Sobbing]

30:27.129 --> 30:36.008
♪♪

30:36.008 --> 30:37.923
[Exhales deeply]

30:37.923 --> 30:46.279
♪♪

30:46.279 --> 30:54.591
♪♪

30:54.591 --> 30:57.203
[Sobs]

30:57.203 --> 30:58.769
[Inhales shakily]

31:03.078 --> 31:04.340
[Inhales shakily]

31:04.340 --> 31:14.785
♪♪

31:14.785 --> 31:17.266
[Breathing heavily]

31:17.266 --> 31:19.529
[Breathing shakily]

31:19.529 --> 31:28.277
♪♪

31:28.277 --> 31:36.982
♪♪

31:36.982 --> 31:45.729
♪♪

31:45.729 --> 31:49.124
"To examine
the causes of life,

31:49.124 --> 31:52.258
we must first have recourse
to death."

31:53.912 --> 31:55.174
Percy: Mary.

31:59.221 --> 32:00.614
Mary?

32:02.268 --> 32:03.530
Mary?

32:05.967 --> 32:07.708
Percy:
Mary. Mary.

32:07.708 --> 32:09.275
Mary, I've edited
your pages.

32:09.275 --> 32:10.972
They're very good.
Truly.

32:10.972 --> 32:13.540
Truly, I never knew you had
such darkness in you.

32:13.540 --> 32:15.411
Mary, Mary,
y-you're angry.

32:16.847 --> 32:19.241
Our fight
last night.

32:19.241 --> 32:21.591
I'm so sorry,
my love.

32:21.591 --> 32:25.378
I've been so caught up in
my writing, my wife, and...

32:27.467 --> 32:28.729
Percy:
Well, you're right.

32:31.210 --> 32:34.517
Then, I go off drinking
with my friends, and...

32:34.517 --> 32:37.259
I should have stayed here,
and apologized to you.

32:37.259 --> 32:41.481
I'm a cad --
a real cad, you know?

32:41.481 --> 32:44.049
I don't mean to
continually disappoint.

32:46.138 --> 32:47.617
I will be better.

32:47.617 --> 32:49.532
Give me love.

32:49.532 --> 32:58.498
♪♪

32:58.498 --> 32:59.847
Hey.

32:59.847 --> 33:07.768
♪♪

33:07.768 --> 33:15.776
♪♪

33:15.776 --> 33:20.346
Mary: "It was this dreary night
in November..."

33:20.346 --> 33:23.610
Man [voiceover]:
"...when I beheld the
accomplishment of all my work."

33:23.610 --> 33:32.010
♪♪

33:32.010 --> 33:33.402
[Thunder crashes]

33:33.402 --> 33:41.802
♪♪

33:41.802 --> 33:50.245
♪♪

33:50.245 --> 33:53.074
Dr. Frankenstein.

33:53.074 --> 34:05.521
♪♪

34:05.521 --> 34:17.925
♪♪

34:17.925 --> 34:30.372
♪♪

34:30.372 --> 34:31.765
[Thunder crashes]

34:34.985 --> 34:37.640
Now this is [???]

34:37.640 --> 34:38.989
Mary.

34:40.295 --> 34:43.472
Claire: Mary.

34:43.472 --> 34:47.085
I said you'd better
shut that window.

34:47.085 --> 34:48.564
Snow is coming.

34:51.524 --> 34:53.743
[Owl hooting]

34:53.743 --> 35:04.841
♪♪

35:04.841 --> 35:15.939
♪♪

35:15.939 --> 35:27.037
♪♪

35:27.037 --> 35:38.136
♪♪

35:38.136 --> 35:49.234
♪♪

35:49.234 --> 36:00.332
♪♪

36:00.332 --> 36:11.430
♪♪

36:11.430 --> 36:15.695
[Indistinct talking]

36:16.304 --> 36:20.787
♪♪

36:20.787 --> 36:23.093
[Baby crying]

36:28.838 --> 36:32.190
[Crying continues]

36:40.372 --> 36:43.984
[Crying continues]

36:46.421 --> 36:50.295
[Crying continues]

36:53.689 --> 36:58.694
[Crying continues]

37:01.567 --> 37:06.702
[Crying continues]

37:10.315 --> 37:15.929
[Crying continues]

37:18.410 --> 37:23.893
[Crying continues]

37:25.547 --> 37:29.812
[Crying continues]

37:35.557 --> 37:37.211
[Exhales sharply]

37:42.564 --> 37:44.131
[Sniffles]

37:58.537 --> 38:00.103
[Gasps]

38:13.726 --> 38:15.249
Percy!

38:16.076 --> 38:17.338
Percy: Mary?

38:24.171 --> 38:25.477
[Whimpers]

38:27.130 --> 38:28.828
[Percy clears throat]

38:31.091 --> 38:32.919
Doctor:
Oh, you're awake.

38:32.919 --> 38:34.616
Claire: What's wrong
with her?

38:34.616 --> 38:36.096
Is it serious?

38:39.317 --> 38:41.101
You're pregnant again, Mary.

38:44.234 --> 38:47.412
No. I can't be.

38:47.412 --> 38:50.023
No, I can't.

38:50.023 --> 38:51.894
Not like this.

38:51.894 --> 38:54.723
It's alright.

38:54.723 --> 38:56.899
You must be much more careful
with this one.

38:56.899 --> 38:58.684
Bed rest, no work.

38:58.684 --> 39:01.295
We don't want another accident,
do we?

39:01.295 --> 39:03.166
And my writing?

39:03.166 --> 39:05.255
Take my advice or not.

39:05.255 --> 39:06.822
It's your life.

39:06.822 --> 39:08.433
I'm merely a doctor.

39:11.479 --> 39:13.568
Perhaps I could talk
to Percy --

39:13.568 --> 39:14.874
No.

39:19.574 --> 39:21.010
Mary:
I'll speak with him.

39:27.626 --> 39:29.410
Percy: A baby?

39:29.410 --> 39:31.717
What di the doctor --
Is it..

39:31.717 --> 39:33.240
Is it safe?

39:34.720 --> 39:36.112
Percy: Mary?

39:36.983 --> 39:38.854
What are we
going to do?

39:38.854 --> 39:41.727
We'll be more careful
this time.

39:41.727 --> 39:43.076
We'll keep you calm --

39:43.076 --> 39:44.904
I mean...

39:44.904 --> 39:46.514
about the baby.

39:50.039 --> 39:54.174
Well, raise it, of course,
just like we planned to before.

39:54.174 --> 39:56.394
Be serious, Percy.

39:56.394 --> 39:57.960
We can't afford
our own costs,

39:57.960 --> 40:00.049
and we're to add
another hungry mouth?

40:00.049 --> 40:01.442
We'll make it work.

40:01.442 --> 40:02.965
No, we won't.

40:05.185 --> 40:09.145
What happened to the girl
I ran away with?

40:09.145 --> 40:11.278
What happened to
"Forget the world"

40:11.278 --> 40:13.759
and "It's worth it
for our love"?

40:13.759 --> 40:16.414
She woke up.

40:16.414 --> 40:19.417
We can figure it out.

40:19.417 --> 40:22.245
What matters is that
we are together,

40:22.245 --> 40:23.725
and I'll take care
of you.

40:23.725 --> 40:25.205
Mary:
For how long?

40:29.209 --> 40:32.255
I left my family
for you.

40:32.255 --> 40:38.261
I have been mocked
and ridiculed for you.

40:38.261 --> 40:40.960
I have watched you
with other women,

40:40.960 --> 40:45.094
and forgiven you for...

40:45.094 --> 40:48.707
for...

40:48.707 --> 40:52.406
And all I ask for
in return...

40:52.406 --> 40:54.843
is for security --

40:54.843 --> 40:57.237
for money enough to eat,

40:57.237 --> 40:59.935
for you to love me
as I love you.

41:02.851 --> 41:04.549
Is that really so evil?

41:18.954 --> 41:20.521
Percy: Please don't
do this.

41:22.958 --> 41:28.007
I cannot lose another love,
another child.

41:31.837 --> 41:35.971
If marriage is the only
solution, then so be it.

41:35.971 --> 41:37.886
Mary: Don't say it
like that.

41:41.324 --> 41:44.371
Doesn't matter
how I say it.

41:44.371 --> 41:46.547
What's done is done.

41:46.547 --> 41:52.814
[Henry Purcell's "Dido's Lament"
plays]

41:52.814 --> 41:58.385
♪ When I am laid ♪

41:58.385 --> 42:05.435
♪ Am laid in earth ♪

42:05.435 --> 42:12.138
♪ May my wrongs create ♪

42:12.138 --> 42:15.881
♪ No trouble ♪

42:15.881 --> 42:26.892
♪ No trouble
in thy breast ♪

42:26.892 --> 42:30.678
♪ Remember me ♪

42:33.768 --> 42:37.206
♪ Remember me ♪

42:40.079 --> 42:45.475
♪ But o-o-o-oh ♪

42:45.475 --> 42:51.177
♪ Forget my fate ♪

42:51.177 --> 42:54.528
♪ Remember me ♪

42:54.528 --> 42:58.445
♪ But o-o-o-oh ♪

42:58.445 --> 43:04.886
♪ Forget my fate ♪

43:11.240 --> 43:21.337
♪♪

43:21.337 --> 43:31.434
♪♪

43:31.434 --> 43:41.531
♪♪

43:41.531 --> 43:44.143
Mary: Claire?

43:44.143 --> 43:45.405
Claire?

43:45.405 --> 43:53.369
♪♪

43:53.369 --> 43:55.023
Claire, sister,
is that you?

43:55.023 --> 44:01.116
♪♪

44:01.116 --> 44:04.076
[Gasps]Victor.

44:04.076 --> 44:07.470
Elizabeth.

44:07.470 --> 44:08.820
Oh, Elizabeth.

44:08.820 --> 44:15.478
♪♪

44:15.478 --> 44:18.264
"The saintly soul
of Elizabeth

44:18.264 --> 44:23.704
shone like the street glance
of her celestial eyes.

44:23.704 --> 44:28.143
She was the living spirit
of love and femininity,

44:28.143 --> 44:31.799
and Victor loved her."

44:31.799 --> 44:33.453
[Victor speaking indistinctly]

44:33.453 --> 44:40.503
♪♪

44:40.503 --> 44:43.028
Don't leave us now, Mary.

44:43.028 --> 44:46.553
The story's
just beginning.

44:46.553 --> 44:50.296
"She weeps continually,

44:50.296 --> 44:52.428
and accuses herself unjustly

44:52.428 --> 44:54.169
as the cause
of William's death."

44:54.169 --> 44:55.518
Percy?
-I'm shaking.

44:55.518 --> 44:57.172
Percy.
-Night is coming.

44:57.172 --> 44:58.391
[Gasps]

44:58.391 --> 44:59.697
You hear me?

45:01.873 --> 45:03.222
Come on.

45:03.222 --> 45:05.093
Let's get inside, yeah?

45:08.836 --> 45:10.098
I thought of
a new sequence.

45:10.098 --> 45:11.926
That's good.
Very good.

45:11.926 --> 45:17.366
Percy: But darling, could you
not pause the writing for a bit?

45:17.366 --> 45:19.891
Claire says you need bed rest
until the birth.

45:19.891 --> 45:22.545
Mary:
Until the birth?

45:22.545 --> 45:25.244
Why, that's absurd.
What on Earth would I do?

45:25.244 --> 45:27.159
Well, it's only
a few months.

45:29.204 --> 45:32.338
Don't forget,
I've done something for you,

45:32.338 --> 45:36.516
and you must take care,
for me.

45:36.516 --> 45:39.954
You're both going to hold this
over my head forever, then.

45:39.954 --> 45:42.391
Aren't you?

45:42.391 --> 45:43.871
Mary.

45:49.181 --> 45:53.228
I-I want to
make this work.

45:53.228 --> 45:54.752
Please.

46:11.551 --> 46:23.302
♪♪

46:29.264 --> 46:36.750
♪♪

46:36.750 --> 46:38.012
[Liquid pours]

46:38.012 --> 46:48.588
♪♪

46:48.588 --> 46:59.207
♪♪

46:59.207 --> 47:01.340
Can you stop?

47:01.340 --> 47:02.558
Please?

47:02.558 --> 47:13.526
♪♪

47:13.526 --> 47:24.537
♪♪

47:24.537 --> 47:26.321
Go home to Mary.

47:29.281 --> 47:30.760
I would if I could.

47:36.418 --> 47:37.811
Percy:
Mary, stop it.

47:37.811 --> 47:39.465
Mary. Mary.

47:42.294 --> 47:44.774
Mary:
Don't talk.

47:44.774 --> 47:46.298
Just touch me.

47:46.298 --> 47:53.218
♪♪

47:53.218 --> 47:55.524
[Mary moaning]

47:55.524 --> 47:57.048
I'm alright.
-I hurt you?

47:57.048 --> 47:58.484
Mary:
I'm alright.

48:01.182 --> 48:03.968
Percy:
Go to bed, Mary.

48:03.968 --> 48:06.057
Go back to bed.

48:06.057 --> 48:12.498
♪♪

48:12.498 --> 48:18.983
♪♪

48:18.983 --> 48:21.028
Mary.

48:21.028 --> 48:25.641
♪♪

48:25.641 --> 48:27.078
[Gasps]

48:27.078 --> 48:28.557
Percy: Stop, stop, stop,
stop, stop, stop.

48:28.557 --> 48:30.255
Wake up. Wake up.

48:32.735 --> 48:34.041
Percy: I'm sorry.

48:39.090 --> 48:40.656
-Percy.
-Percy!

48:40.656 --> 48:42.006
Claire: Mary.

48:44.051 --> 48:45.357
Mary.

48:45.357 --> 48:47.794
Are you alright?
Are you alright?

48:49.709 --> 48:50.971
Shh.

48:50.971 --> 48:52.799
[Sobbing]

48:57.543 --> 49:00.459
[Bell rings]

49:00.459 --> 49:03.549
[Footsteps approaching]

49:12.514 --> 49:15.691
Where is he?

49:15.691 --> 49:18.433
Tell him to come here.

49:18.433 --> 49:20.522
He's not here.

49:20.522 --> 49:24.309
What do you mean,
he's not here?

49:24.309 --> 49:27.747
Where else would he be?

49:27.747 --> 49:29.662
Is he at Byron's?

49:29.662 --> 49:32.143
He hates this, too.

49:32.143 --> 49:34.188
He asks me to stay.

49:34.188 --> 49:36.364
I stay.

49:36.364 --> 49:38.758
He asks me to lay
in this bloody bed,

49:38.758 --> 49:40.238
and I lay.

49:40.238 --> 49:45.460
He even asks me to stop writing,
and I stop.

49:45.460 --> 49:47.680
What else does he need?

49:52.946 --> 49:55.949
♪♪

49:55.949 --> 49:57.646
[Screams]

49:57.646 --> 49:59.387
Claire:
You must push, Mary.

49:59.387 --> 50:02.347
[Breathing heavily]

50:02.347 --> 50:04.131
Where is he?

50:04.131 --> 50:05.741
Where is the doctor?

50:05.741 --> 50:08.527
Coming.
They come.

50:08.527 --> 50:10.659
Now, push, Mary.

50:10.659 --> 50:12.879
Push.

50:12.879 --> 50:15.360
[Screams]

50:15.360 --> 50:16.796
I can't.

50:16.796 --> 50:19.233
I can't.

50:19.233 --> 50:20.495
Where is Percy?

50:20.495 --> 50:22.019
Bring him to me, please.

50:22.019 --> 50:23.716
Mary, listen to me.

50:23.716 --> 50:25.152
If you do not push,

50:25.152 --> 50:27.502
you will kill this child,
and likely yourself.

50:27.502 --> 50:28.764
Now, get ahold
of yourself.

50:28.764 --> 50:30.331
[Grunts]

50:30.331 --> 50:31.767
Push.

50:31.767 --> 50:34.248
[Breathing heavily]

50:39.036 --> 50:42.300
[Gasps]

50:42.300 --> 50:45.085
[Groans]

50:45.085 --> 50:46.434
Percy.

50:46.434 --> 50:49.350
Victor: It is me,
if you wish it.

50:49.350 --> 50:51.265
No, not you.

50:51.265 --> 50:53.398
Please, God, not you.

50:53.398 --> 50:55.487
I've missed you.

50:55.487 --> 50:58.794
No. No. No.
I want my husband.

50:58.794 --> 51:00.057
I'm what you've got.

51:00.057 --> 51:02.102
I want Percy.

51:02.102 --> 51:03.364
I want...

51:03.364 --> 51:04.626
[Groans]

51:04.626 --> 51:06.019
Do you want to die?

51:10.850 --> 51:12.243
Then, push.

51:12.852 --> 51:16.595
I'm here, and I will never
leave you again -- not like him.

51:16.595 --> 51:22.775
♪♪

51:22.775 --> 51:26.344
[Groaning]

51:26.344 --> 51:27.736
[Inhales sharply]

51:30.130 --> 51:32.306
[Screams]

51:34.221 --> 51:35.527
[Squelching]

51:35.527 --> 51:36.963
[Gasping]

51:36.963 --> 51:45.102
♪♪

51:45.102 --> 51:46.712
He's beautiful, Mary.

51:46.712 --> 51:48.105
[Gasps]

51:50.977 --> 51:52.413
Claire.

51:52.413 --> 51:54.285
Wait -- Wait.

52:00.943 --> 52:02.336
Victor.

52:05.687 --> 52:07.080
Victor.

52:14.653 --> 52:17.786
[Baby crying in distance]

52:21.225 --> 52:32.323
♪♪

52:32.323 --> 52:43.769
♪♪

52:51.124 --> 52:53.605
It lives.

52:53.605 --> 52:55.824
He's hungry.

52:55.824 --> 52:57.565
Mary: Not now.

52:57.565 --> 52:58.914
Claire: Mary...

52:58.914 --> 53:01.395
[Baby fussing]

53:33.166 --> 53:34.602
Take him away.

53:34.602 --> 53:36.691
Take him away.

53:36.691 --> 53:38.780
Take him.

53:38.780 --> 53:40.042
[Inhales shakily]

53:40.042 --> 53:42.393
That's not my baby.

53:42.393 --> 53:44.003
Of course he is.

53:44.003 --> 53:47.006
And he's hungry,
longing for you.

53:47.006 --> 53:48.790
Take him away, Claire.

53:58.583 --> 53:59.975
Wait.

54:02.630 --> 54:03.979
What of Percy?

54:08.114 --> 54:10.986
Bring him home
to me, Claire.

54:10.986 --> 54:14.251
Tell him...

54:14.251 --> 54:18.211
Tell him he has a son
who's in need of a name.

54:18.211 --> 54:21.301
I can't go back there.

54:21.301 --> 54:24.173
Lord Byron...

54:24.173 --> 54:25.610
he ended it.

54:41.800 --> 54:43.062
[Gasps]

54:43.062 --> 54:44.846
[Inhales shakily]

54:54.987 --> 54:57.119
I thought you left me.

55:00.906 --> 55:03.256
[Inhales sharply,
exhales sharply]

55:03.256 --> 55:07.391
[Inhales sharply,
exhales shakily]

55:07.391 --> 55:09.915
I have lost him, Victor.

55:13.527 --> 55:15.660
I have lost it all.

55:30.152 --> 55:34.026
Mary: "We continued to search
for him until night fell,

55:34.026 --> 55:35.854
when Elizabeth conjectured

55:35.854 --> 55:40.032
that he might have returned
to the house.

55:40.032 --> 55:42.426
We went into the house
with torches

55:42.426 --> 55:46.038
for I could not rest when I
thought that my sweet boy

55:46.038 --> 55:48.606
had lost himself,
and was exposed

55:48.606 --> 55:52.218
to all the damps and dews
of the night.

55:52.218 --> 55:55.526
About 5:00 in the morning I
discovered my lovely boy,

55:55.526 --> 55:59.921
whom weeks before I had seen
blooming and active in health,

55:59.921 --> 56:05.579
stretched on the floor,
livid and motionless.

56:05.579 --> 56:09.366
the print of the murder's
finger was on his neck."

56:09.366 --> 56:12.456
Mary.
Is she alright?

56:12.456 --> 56:14.545
She's alright.

56:14.545 --> 56:17.025
And you have a baby boy.

56:17.025 --> 56:20.855
"Never will I give up my search
for this horrible creature,

56:20.855 --> 56:23.423
not until he
or I perish."

56:23.423 --> 56:25.033
Byron:
"Fare thee well.

56:25.033 --> 56:28.297
And if forever, then still
forever, fare thee well."

56:28.297 --> 56:30.561
Percy: Stop it.
Get off of her, you savage.

56:30.561 --> 56:34.565
Mary: "Then, with ecstasy,
will I join my Elizabeth,

56:34.565 --> 56:39.352
who even now prepares me for
the reward of my tedious toil

56:39.352 --> 56:43.138
and horrible pilgrimage."

56:43.138 --> 56:45.619
[Door closes]

56:45.619 --> 56:47.578
Percy!

56:47.578 --> 56:48.927
[Baby crying]

56:48.927 --> 56:50.276
You're here.

56:52.670 --> 56:54.498
Claire: Can't you hear
him crying?

56:54.498 --> 56:56.369
He's only
just started.

56:57.631 --> 56:59.067
Percy:
I have a baby.

57:01.156 --> 57:03.942
Oh.

57:03.942 --> 57:06.553
He has your eyes.

57:06.553 --> 57:10.514
We should name him "William,"
after your father.

57:13.908 --> 57:15.170
Give him here.

57:17.172 --> 57:19.392
Oh, my.
He's sick.

57:27.705 --> 57:29.010
Mary:
Where have you been?

57:32.144 --> 57:34.102
Percy: I lost track
of time.

57:34.102 --> 57:35.495
For three weeks?

57:45.766 --> 57:47.159
Forgive me.

57:48.900 --> 57:51.032
You won't leave me again,
will you?

57:52.947 --> 57:55.733
I'll die.

57:55.733 --> 57:57.256
I know it.
I'll die.

57:57.256 --> 57:59.693
Percy:
Have you been writing?

57:59.693 --> 58:03.610
I waited,
just as I said I would.

58:06.004 --> 58:12.314
[Birds chirping]

58:12.314 --> 58:14.012
Claire:
Be gentle with William.

58:14.012 --> 58:17.494
You know he's not
feeling well.

58:17.494 --> 58:20.235
[William crying]

58:20.235 --> 58:22.020
Mary, do you know
what you're doing?

58:22.020 --> 58:24.718
Of course I do.
I'm his mother.

58:26.633 --> 58:29.027
Shh.

58:29.027 --> 58:31.769
Percy, look how sweet he is
in my arms.

58:31.769 --> 58:33.205
Our little boy.

58:36.861 --> 58:38.689
[Sighs]

58:38.689 --> 58:40.386
Mary, give him here.Damn it, Claire!

58:40.386 --> 58:41.735
[Crying]

58:41.735 --> 58:44.651
Give him to Claire.

58:44.651 --> 58:45.957
Please.

58:45.957 --> 58:47.393
[Coughs]

58:47.393 --> 58:49.526
[Crying stops]

59:06.064 --> 59:07.369
Claire: Mary.

1:00:01.510 --> 1:00:03.295
Mary:
Make love to me.

1:00:10.128 --> 1:00:11.608
Percy:
I'm tired.

1:00:15.786 --> 1:00:17.614
I'm tired.

1:00:17.614 --> 1:00:19.137
Go to sleep.

1:00:22.444 --> 1:00:23.750
[Sighs]

1:00:27.319 --> 1:00:28.799
[Exhales deeply]

1:00:33.586 --> 1:00:35.980
Victor:
Lonely, lonely Mary.

1:00:39.070 --> 1:00:40.724
You can't be here.

1:00:40.724 --> 1:00:47.078
♪♪

1:00:47.078 --> 1:00:48.775
I can't want you.

1:00:48.775 --> 1:00:59.786
♪♪

1:00:59.786 --> 1:01:10.754
♪♪

1:01:10.754 --> 1:01:21.765
♪♪

1:01:21.765 --> 1:01:32.732
♪♪

1:01:32.732 --> 1:01:43.743
♪♪

1:01:43.743 --> 1:01:45.092
[Gasps]

1:01:45.092 --> 1:01:48.443
[Breathing heavily]

1:01:48.443 --> 1:01:50.097
[Moans]

1:01:50.097 --> 1:01:52.970
[Breathing heavily]

1:01:52.970 --> 1:02:05.069
♪♪

1:02:05.069 --> 1:02:17.168
♪♪

1:02:17.168 --> 1:02:29.267
♪♪

1:02:29.267 --> 1:02:36.361
"The blood flowed freely
in my veins,

1:02:36.361 --> 1:02:39.451
but a weight of despair
and remorse

1:02:39.451 --> 1:02:43.847
pressed upon my heart
which nothing could remove."

1:02:46.632 --> 1:02:51.071
"I wandered
like an evil spirit,

1:02:51.071 --> 1:02:55.032
for I had committed deeds of
mischief beyond description --

1:02:55.032 --> 1:02:57.904
horrible.

1:02:57.904 --> 1:03:02.474
And more -- much more --
was yet ahead."

1:03:02.474 --> 1:03:09.263
♪♪

1:03:09.263 --> 1:03:10.569
Dear God.

1:03:13.485 --> 1:03:15.356
Percy: Mary?

1:03:15.356 --> 1:03:16.705
Mary, what's happened?

1:03:31.764 --> 1:03:35.246
[Birds chirping]

1:03:35.246 --> 1:03:37.944
"I feared the vengeance
of the disappointed fiend,

1:03:37.944 --> 1:03:40.294
yet I was unable to overcome
my repugnance

1:03:40.294 --> 1:03:42.557
to the task which was
enjoined me."

1:03:46.213 --> 1:03:48.172
Mary.

1:03:48.172 --> 1:03:50.565
I think it's time for you
to take a break.

1:03:50.565 --> 1:03:53.046
It would do you good to get away
from this cottage.

1:03:53.046 --> 1:03:56.223
Or would it do you good
to have William all to yourself?

1:03:56.223 --> 1:03:58.008
Mary, please.

1:03:58.008 --> 1:03:59.923
Let's go to Byron's,
just for the weekend, yeah?

1:03:59.923 --> 1:04:01.663
I'm almost done.

1:04:01.663 --> 1:04:03.274
The final chapter.

1:04:06.190 --> 1:04:08.975
You can stop now, Mary.

1:04:08.975 --> 1:04:13.023
All the bills are paid,
food is on the table.

1:04:13.023 --> 1:04:14.285
There's no need
for more pages.

1:04:14.285 --> 1:04:15.590
Leave me be.

1:04:17.766 --> 1:04:19.029
Mary.

1:04:28.603 --> 1:04:30.779
Mary, we beg you.

1:04:32.172 --> 1:04:35.784
"I took refuge
in most perfect solitude,

1:04:35.784 --> 1:04:37.612
whole days
on the lake alone,

1:04:37.612 --> 1:04:43.618
listening to the rippling of
the waves, silent and listless."

1:04:43.618 --> 1:04:46.708
Do you hear yourself?
You're sounding mad.

1:04:46.708 --> 1:04:48.536
And your jealousy
is sounding childish.

1:04:48.536 --> 1:04:49.886
Jealousy?

1:04:49.886 --> 1:04:51.496
You wish to stop
these words.

1:04:51.496 --> 1:04:54.151
Why?
Because I challenge you?

1:04:54.151 --> 1:04:56.022
Because the great
Percy Shelley

1:04:56.022 --> 1:04:58.546
may have finally found
some competition?

1:04:58.546 --> 1:05:01.332
Sure. Fine.

1:05:01.332 --> 1:05:03.725
You want to be alone?
So be it.

1:05:05.771 --> 1:05:07.816
What do you mean?

1:05:07.816 --> 1:05:09.079
Percy!

1:05:09.079 --> 1:05:10.471
Claire: Let me.

1:05:12.691 --> 1:05:17.522
[Indistinct shouting
in distance]

1:05:17.522 --> 1:05:19.872
[William crying]

1:05:22.005 --> 1:05:24.137
Mary: Percy, wait!

1:05:24.137 --> 1:05:25.617
I'll stop.

1:05:25.617 --> 1:05:27.445
I can. I will.

1:05:27.445 --> 1:05:29.360
[William crying in distance]

1:05:35.061 --> 1:05:45.898
♪♪

1:05:45.898 --> 1:05:56.691
♪♪

1:05:56.691 --> 1:05:58.258
[Floor creaking]

1:05:58.258 --> 1:06:10.270
♪♪

1:06:10.270 --> 1:06:11.619
[Gasps]

1:06:17.799 --> 1:06:21.107
♪♪

1:06:21.107 --> 1:06:23.631
Victor, make this end.
I must stop.

1:06:23.631 --> 1:06:27.853
Victor: I have worked hard
for years for the sole purpose

1:06:27.853 --> 1:06:32.640
of infusing life
into an inanimate body.

1:06:32.640 --> 1:06:37.906
And here it is
before me...

1:06:37.906 --> 1:06:39.343
my creature.

1:06:42.172 --> 1:06:47.612
♪♪

1:06:47.612 --> 1:06:50.049
My creature --
she lives!

1:06:50.049 --> 1:06:51.442
Percy:
I can't leave her.

1:06:52.617 --> 1:06:54.401
You have to
do something.

1:06:58.797 --> 1:07:01.495
How have you grown years
in just months, moppet?

1:07:02.888 --> 1:07:04.629
I love this family.

1:07:04.629 --> 1:07:06.370
I can't watch it burn.

1:07:06.370 --> 1:07:08.981
Please, Percy, we must
take William to a safer home.

1:07:08.981 --> 1:07:10.896
[Footsteps approaching]

1:07:10.896 --> 1:07:13.551
Mary?

1:07:13.551 --> 1:07:16.162
He sleeps.

1:07:16.162 --> 1:07:21.515
He was crying,
but now he sleeps.

1:07:21.515 --> 1:07:22.908
No.

1:07:22.908 --> 1:07:24.170
No.

1:07:24.170 --> 1:07:25.911
[William crying]

1:07:25.911 --> 1:07:27.217
Mary, what's happened?

1:07:27.217 --> 1:07:28.609
I found him.

1:07:28.609 --> 1:07:31.177
He was...so still.

1:07:38.663 --> 1:07:40.795
Give him back to me!
He cries for his mother.

1:07:40.795 --> 1:07:43.320
-What did you do?
-She's killed him.

1:07:43.320 --> 1:07:44.886
What are you
talking about?

1:07:44.886 --> 1:07:46.236
Listen to his cries.

1:07:46.236 --> 1:07:47.715
-The child is --
-...dead, Mary.

1:07:47.715 --> 1:07:49.021
He's not dead.

1:07:49.021 --> 1:07:50.327
Mary, he's gone.

1:07:50.327 --> 1:07:51.719
Mary:
Cry for them.

1:07:51.719 --> 1:07:53.721
Cry louder so that
they will hear you.

1:07:53.721 --> 1:07:54.983
[Crying stops]

1:07:54.983 --> 1:07:56.855
[Gasps]

1:07:56.855 --> 1:07:58.900
Victor, what's happened?

1:07:58.900 --> 1:08:00.424
Restore his life.

1:08:00.424 --> 1:08:01.990
Do for him what you did
for your creature.

1:08:01.990 --> 1:08:03.383
Percy: Mary, stop.

1:08:03.383 --> 1:08:05.429
My dear, I can't.

1:08:12.218 --> 1:08:16.353
♪♪

1:08:16.353 --> 1:08:17.658
Mary, stop.

1:08:17.658 --> 1:08:19.356
Please, sister.

1:08:19.356 --> 1:08:21.880
Let me hold him.

1:08:21.880 --> 1:08:23.577
Let me hold my baby.

1:08:23.577 --> 1:08:25.231
Aah!

1:08:27.668 --> 1:08:29.235
No.

1:08:31.977 --> 1:08:33.544
No.

1:08:33.544 --> 1:08:34.980
No.

1:08:37.417 --> 1:08:40.768
[Sobbing]

1:08:40.768 --> 1:08:42.074
No, not again.

1:08:42.074 --> 1:08:43.423
Not again.

1:08:43.423 --> 1:08:45.643
Mary, close your eyes, Mary.

1:08:45.643 --> 1:08:53.520
♪♪

1:08:53.520 --> 1:09:01.311
♪♪

1:09:01.311 --> 1:09:04.183
[Sobbing]

1:09:04.183 --> 1:09:13.061
♪♪

1:09:13.671 --> 1:09:22.158
♪♪

1:09:22.158 --> 1:09:30.601
♪♪

1:09:30.601 --> 1:09:32.429
Victor:
Lock yourself in.

1:09:32.429 --> 1:09:33.778
Open it for no one
but me.

1:09:33.778 --> 1:09:35.823
What's going on?

1:09:35.823 --> 1:09:38.391
I have a growing feeling
that it is not safe.

1:09:38.391 --> 1:09:40.045
My creature is trying
to kill me.

1:09:40.045 --> 1:09:41.394
Now, hurry. Go.

1:09:44.919 --> 1:09:47.922
Woman: Remember.

1:09:47.922 --> 1:09:50.882
I yet have power.

1:09:50.882 --> 1:09:52.449
Yes.

1:09:52.449 --> 1:09:54.668
I can make you so retched

1:09:54.668 --> 1:09:59.195
that the light of day
will be hateful to you.

1:09:59.195 --> 1:10:00.848
What are you
doing here?!

1:10:00.848 --> 1:10:05.766
You are my creator,
but I am your master.

1:10:05.766 --> 1:10:08.943
Now it is the innocent
who will suffer.

1:10:28.615 --> 1:10:29.877
Elizabeth?

1:10:33.707 --> 1:10:35.100
Elizabeth?

1:10:37.450 --> 1:10:39.713
How could you?

1:10:39.713 --> 1:10:43.804
Lifeless and inanimate.

1:10:43.804 --> 1:10:45.284
Bye-bye, Beth.

1:10:45.284 --> 1:10:46.546
Claire: Mary.

1:10:49.114 --> 1:10:50.985
Elizabeth.

1:10:50.985 --> 1:10:52.509
I'm not Elizabeth.

1:10:54.815 --> 1:10:56.339
See me, sister.

1:11:14.095 --> 1:11:18.709
You've been
very ill, Mary.

1:11:18.709 --> 1:11:22.626
We thought it was just the
waiting, but it's much more.

1:11:22.626 --> 1:11:26.238
It's time for you
to see a doctor.

1:11:26.238 --> 1:11:28.066
My child is dead.

1:11:31.722 --> 1:11:33.201
I need rest.

1:11:34.768 --> 1:11:36.640
You need much more
than that.

1:11:40.296 --> 1:11:47.259
♪♪

1:11:47.259 --> 1:11:48.695
Stop.

1:11:51.394 --> 1:11:53.265
This is what you've wanted,
isn't it?

1:11:55.441 --> 1:11:56.877
With me out of the way,

1:11:56.877 --> 1:12:00.054
you'd finally have a family
all to yourself.

1:12:00.054 --> 1:12:01.534
Mary, listen to yourself.

1:12:01.534 --> 1:12:04.015
You've been ever so patient,
sister.

1:12:04.015 --> 1:12:05.277
Come now.
Get up.

1:12:05.277 --> 1:12:09.020
If this house
burdens you so much,

1:12:09.020 --> 1:12:14.112
if my sadness is more than
your feeble mind can understand,

1:12:14.112 --> 1:12:17.898
then it is you
who need to leave.

1:12:17.898 --> 1:12:23.034
Do not forget,
Percy's my husband,

1:12:23.034 --> 1:12:26.516
and you are a guest.

1:12:26.516 --> 1:12:28.561
You are a guest
in our house.

1:12:32.173 --> 1:12:34.045
I can't possibly
try to understand

1:12:34.045 --> 1:12:37.570
the pain you're in...

1:12:37.570 --> 1:12:39.224
but you can't blame me.

1:12:39.224 --> 1:12:41.966
Mary: Do not!

1:12:41.966 --> 1:12:45.448
[Breathing shakily]

1:12:45.448 --> 1:12:46.927
Get out of my house.

1:12:50.931 --> 1:12:52.498
Claire:
Mary, please --

1:12:52.498 --> 1:12:55.588
I won't hear
your voice anymore.

1:12:57.721 --> 1:12:59.505
Where will I go?

1:12:59.505 --> 1:13:01.377
I don't care.

1:13:01.377 --> 1:13:03.683
You are not my sister.

1:13:03.683 --> 1:13:08.732
♪♪

1:13:08.732 --> 1:13:10.037
I never --

1:13:10.037 --> 1:13:11.343
Get out!

1:13:18.568 --> 1:13:20.178
-I'm so sorry.
-Get out.

1:13:23.094 --> 1:13:28.012
[Sobbing]

1:13:33.496 --> 1:13:35.628
Claire.

1:13:35.628 --> 1:13:37.108
[Door closes]

1:13:50.077 --> 1:13:53.646
[Footsteps approaching]

1:14:28.246 --> 1:14:29.552
Mary: Percy?

1:14:52.792 --> 1:14:54.446
Mary:
I want to fix us.

1:15:24.607 --> 1:15:28.828
Shh, shh, shh.

1:15:28.828 --> 1:15:31.091
[Moans]

1:15:31.091 --> 1:15:34.138
[Breathing heavily]

1:15:34.138 --> 1:15:37.924
[Incoherent muttering]

1:15:37.924 --> 1:15:39.535
[Speaks indistinctly]

1:15:41.754 --> 1:15:43.190
That's what we need.

1:15:45.932 --> 1:15:47.325
Another child.

1:15:48.761 --> 1:15:50.197
We'll be together.

1:16:09.260 --> 1:16:11.610
[Birds chirping]

1:16:26.059 --> 1:16:27.844
[Exhales deeply]

1:17:19.983 --> 1:17:21.245
Percy?

1:17:38.175 --> 1:17:39.655
What are you doing,
my love?

1:17:43.746 --> 1:17:45.008
Percy?

1:17:49.229 --> 1:17:52.232
Mary.

1:17:52.232 --> 1:17:53.712
Is it you?

1:18:13.123 --> 1:18:14.864
[Gasps]

1:18:14.864 --> 1:18:16.866
Victor.

1:18:16.866 --> 1:18:19.390
Geez, Mary.
You and your fits.

1:18:19.390 --> 1:18:21.348
You...

1:18:21.348 --> 1:18:23.394
You...

1:18:23.394 --> 1:18:24.743
Always you.

1:18:28.355 --> 1:18:31.271
[Breathing heavily]

1:18:31.794 --> 1:18:33.230
Jesus, Mary.

1:18:36.799 --> 1:18:38.278
[Exhales shakily]

1:18:38.278 --> 1:18:39.715
[Victor laughing]

1:18:39.715 --> 1:18:41.151
Stop.

1:18:41.151 --> 1:18:42.587
Stop.

1:18:42.587 --> 1:18:44.415
[Breathing heavily]

1:18:45.808 --> 1:18:47.244
I thought this
might help.

1:18:51.727 --> 1:18:53.598
What have you done?
What have you done?!

1:18:53.598 --> 1:18:54.817
I was just
trying to help.

1:18:54.817 --> 1:18:56.209
I was just trying
to help.

1:18:58.646 --> 1:19:01.780
You spiteful,
jealous man.

1:19:01.780 --> 1:19:03.477
How could you?

1:19:03.477 --> 1:19:05.088
My novel!

1:19:05.088 --> 1:19:06.480
That was my world!

1:19:06.480 --> 1:19:08.744
I was your world.

1:19:08.744 --> 1:19:10.006
But you left me.

1:19:10.006 --> 1:19:11.355
I left you?

1:19:14.401 --> 1:19:16.012
Ileft you?

1:19:17.100 --> 1:19:19.929
You're right.

1:19:19.929 --> 1:19:22.322
I drove you
to this madness --

1:19:22.322 --> 1:19:24.150
just like I did before,
with her.

1:19:27.240 --> 1:19:29.373
I am not mad.

1:19:29.373 --> 1:19:30.940
I choose this.

1:19:37.294 --> 1:19:38.774
You can't leave me.
You can't leave me.

1:19:38.774 --> 1:19:40.210
You wouldn't.
-Stop.

1:19:40.210 --> 1:19:42.386
I love you.Then let me go.

1:19:45.824 --> 1:19:47.260
Percy, stop!

1:19:49.393 --> 1:19:50.742
Percy, please.

1:19:51.961 --> 1:19:53.266
Percy, wait.

1:19:54.920 --> 1:19:56.226
Percy.

1:19:56.226 --> 1:20:08.499
♪♪

1:20:08.499 --> 1:20:10.240
We can fix this.

1:20:10.240 --> 1:20:11.850
There's nothing left to fix.

1:20:13.591 --> 1:20:17.290
Only fragments of the woman
I loved remain in you.

1:20:17.290 --> 1:20:18.814
You're a monster, Mary.

1:20:23.949 --> 1:20:25.777
[Victor laughing]

1:20:25.777 --> 1:20:33.219
♪♪

1:20:33.219 --> 1:20:40.618
♪♪

1:20:40.618 --> 1:20:42.054
No!

1:20:42.054 --> 1:20:49.540
♪♪

1:20:49.540 --> 1:20:50.846
[Victor laughing]

1:20:50.846 --> 1:20:52.499
We were born for this.

1:20:52.499 --> 1:20:56.547
We were made to withstand
this pain and torment --

1:20:56.547 --> 1:20:58.375
for each other.

1:20:58.375 --> 1:21:00.072
[Gasps]

1:21:00.072 --> 1:21:03.162
[Breathing heavily]

1:21:09.734 --> 1:21:10.996
Oh, God.

1:21:25.010 --> 1:21:28.492
♪♪

1:21:28.492 --> 1:21:30.973
Percy.

1:21:30.973 --> 1:21:32.278
Percy.

1:21:32.278 --> 1:21:35.368
[Breathing heavily]

1:21:35.368 --> 1:21:37.588
Percy!

1:21:37.588 --> 1:21:40.504
[Breathing heavily]

1:21:45.944 --> 1:21:47.815
Percy!

1:21:47.815 --> 1:21:57.521
♪♪

1:21:57.521 --> 1:22:02.178
[Sobbing]

1:22:05.007 --> 1:22:11.404
♪♪

1:22:11.404 --> 1:22:17.758
♪♪

1:22:17.758 --> 1:22:19.325
Victor.

1:22:19.325 --> 1:22:26.593
♪♪

1:22:26.593 --> 1:22:29.683
[Sobbing]

1:22:29.683 --> 1:22:41.739
♪♪

1:22:41.739 --> 1:22:53.794
♪♪

1:22:53.794 --> 1:22:56.667
Mary: "Beware.

1:22:56.667 --> 1:23:02.934
For I am fearless,
and therefore powerful.

1:23:02.934 --> 1:23:09.245
For if I cannot inspire love,
I will cause fear."

1:23:09.245 --> 1:23:18.602
♪♪

1:23:18.602 --> 1:23:28.003
♪♪

1:23:28.003 --> 1:23:30.353
Percy?

1:23:30.353 --> 1:23:35.967
♪♪

1:23:35.967 --> 1:23:37.664
Yes.

1:23:40.015 --> 1:23:41.538
Shh.

1:23:44.758 --> 1:23:49.763
There you are,
my sweet boy.

1:23:49.763 --> 1:23:52.766
[Chuckles]

1:23:52.766 --> 1:23:56.683
"Frankenstein"
is selling well.

1:23:56.683 --> 1:23:58.946
Just as you said.

1:23:58.946 --> 1:24:01.514
I told you the pages
weren't necessary.

1:24:01.514 --> 1:24:09.609
♪♪

1:24:09.609 --> 1:24:14.440
We make a
beautiful family.

1:24:14.440 --> 1:24:15.746
Don't we?

1:24:15.746 --> 1:24:23.536
♪♪

1:24:23.536 --> 1:24:25.277
[Baby crying]

1:24:25.277 --> 1:24:36.375
♪♪

1:24:36.375 --> 1:24:47.473
♪♪

1:24:47.473 --> 1:24:58.615
♪♪

1:24:58.615 --> 1:25:09.669
♪♪

1:25:09.669 --> 1:25:20.767
♪♪

1:25:20.767 --> 1:25:31.865
♪♪

1:25:31.865 --> 1:25:42.963
♪♪

1:25:42.963 --> 1:25:54.061
♪♪

1:25:54.061 --> 1:26:05.203
♪♪

1:26:05.203 --> 1:26:16.301
♪♪

1:26:16.301 --> 1:26:27.399
♪♪

